The paper deals with the problem of exact recovery of sparse vectors, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI). The use of lp-relaxation, Orthogonal Matching Pursuit (OMP), and Orthogonal Least Squares (OLS) also suggests these categories.
